# Hermes Workspace — Agent Control Panel
## Open-source command center for AI agent swarms

**URL:** https://hermes-workspace.com | **GitHub:** github.com/outsourc-e/hermes-workspace | **Stars:** 2,000+ | **License:** MIT

---

## WHAT IT IS

Hermes Workspace is an open-source web UI that turns a raw Hermes agent into a full **mission control center**. One dashboard to chat, manage memory, browse skills, run a terminal, and — most importantly — **orchestrate swarms of sub-agents** with live oversight.

This is the "control panel" Eric demoed on April 28. One install command, fully local.

---

## CORE CAPABILITIES

### The 6 Screens
1. **Multi-model chat** — Claude, GPT, Gemini, Codex, Ollama in one thread
2. **Memory & skills** — 100+ skills, persistent memory, live browse/edit
3. **Integrated terminal** — PTY in the browser, no leaving the workspace
4. **Real-time tool cards** — Watch every tool call live, approve/abort each one
5. **Mobile-first PWA** — Full parity on desktop/tablet/phone
6. **Conductor + Operations** — Spawn parallel sub-agents, live worker grid, operations console

### Orchestration Features
- **Mission-based workflow** — Define a mission, spawn multiple sub-agents on it
- **Conductor** — Master agent that coordinates sub-agents
- **Checkpoint gates** — Review before approving agent actions
- **Autopilot mode** — Agents run without asking, human can override
- **Cron scheduling** — Time-based mission triggers
- **Token analytics** — Real-time usage tracking per agent
- **WebSocket streaming** — Live updates, no polling

### Provider Support
400+ NOS models, OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, local models

